==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enstatite
<hw>En"sta*tite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named fr. Gr. <?/
an adversary, because infusible before the blowpipe.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of the pyroxene group, orthorhombic in
crystallization; often fibrous and massive; color grayish white or
greenish. It is a silicate of magnesia with some iron. Bronzite is a
ferriferous variety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enstatitic</ent>⟦br⟧
